{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5363816b-3296-4b00-8722-43f32dba2fe2","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x changed the default test runner** from VSTest to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP)**. Since your CI uses `vstest.console`, it can't discover tests anymore because the VSTest adapter is no longer wired up by default.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 – Keep vstest.console (quick fix)\n\nAdd `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` to your project:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/4.1.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n### Option 2 – Migrate to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (recommended)\n\nReplace `vstest.console` in your CI with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nor run the test executable directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --results-directory ./TestResults\n```\n\nMTP is the forward-looking runner with better performance and built-in parallel execution. Option 2 is the recommended long-term path.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3a99761c-0b55-4c07-b403-0e1f8151404e","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a known breaking change in MSTest.Sdk. Let me explain what changed.\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, MSTest introduced support for Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) as an alternative to VSTest. However, in MSTest.Sdk 3.x, VSTest remained the default runner.\n\nIn MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0+, the default runner changed from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This means `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests because the test project no longer includes the VSTest adapter/infrastructure by default.\n\nThe key property is `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` — if you want to continue using vstest.console, you need to set this property. Alternatively, you can migrate your CI pipeline to use `dotnet test` with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (which is the recommended path forward).\n\n\nSo to summarize the fix: either add that UseVSTest property to your project file to restore the old behavior, or update your test runner to use the newer Microsoft.Testing.Platform approach instead.","outputTokens":516,"requestId":"7028:3A9384:4A0BE7:56BECF:69F2C3B8"},"id":"8f00182e-15a8-472a-96c4-620f07dded71","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:51:46.323Z","parentId":"0aaea1ab-aae8-4a82-8475-28be65311551"}
